# API Rules

- Validate all inputs at the boundary with zod — never trust client data
- Return consistent error shapes: `{ error: string, code: string, details?: unknown }`
- Rate limit sensitive endpoints (auth, payment, admin)
- Log request ID, duration, status code, and error name for every response
- Auth middleware runs before business logic — never inline auth checks
- Handle all five cases: success, validation error, auth error, not found, server error
- Document expected request/response shapes in comments or schema files
- Server Actions: use `'use server'`, validate with zod, return `{ data?, error? }`
- Never expose internal error messages to the client — log internally, return generic message
- Use HTTP verbs correctly: GET (read), POST (create), PUT (replace), PATCH (update), DELETE
- Add `Cache-Control` headers explicitly — don't rely on framework defaults
